To find how fast the mosquito population is changing after 4 days, differentiate A(t) and then evaluate the derivative at t = 4.

1. Differentiate A(t):
   A(t) = 1000 e^{0.3t}

   dA/dt = 1000·0.3·e^{0.3t} = 300 e^{0.3t}

2. Evaluate at t = 4:
   dA/dt|_{t=4} = 300 e^{0.3·4} = 300 e^{1.2}

3. Numerical value (using e^{1.2} ≈ 3.3201):
   dA/dt|_{t=4} ≈ 300 (3.3201) ≈ 996 mosquitoes per day

Hence, after 4 days the mosquito population is increasing at a rate of about 996 mosquitoes per day (exactly 300 e^{1.2}).
